    <article class="prose-editorial cs-body" set:html={`<h3><b>Educational Case Study Disclosure</b></h3><p>This case study is hypothetical and for educational purposes only. Scenarios, borrower profiles, loan terms, interest rates, and outcomes are illustrative examples and do not represent current offers or guaranteed terms.</p><p>For specific details including down payment requirements, closing cost estimates, interest rate details, closing cost breakdowns, payment calculations, cash-to-close estimates, or an official Loan Estimate, it is highly recommended you<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a meeting with one of our licensed mortgage advisors</a>.</p><p><b>Learn more:</b></p><ul><li><a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1026/24/">Asset-based loan purchase Reg Z advertising requirements (§1026.24)</a> – CFPB official regulation</li><li><a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-12/chapter-X/part-1026">Asset-based loan purchase Reg Z full text and compliance</a> – Electronic Code of Federal Regulations</li><li><a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1026/interp-24/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Official asset-based loan purchase advertising interpretations (§1026.24)</a> – CFPB interpretations</li><li><a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-12/chapter-X/part-1014" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Asset-based loan purchase MAP Rule (Reg N) mortgage advertising</a> – Mortgage advertising rules</li><li><a href="https://www.nmlsconsumeraccess.org/">NMLS Consumer Access – Verify asset-based loan purchase lender licensure</a></li></ul><p>Actual loan terms vary by credit profile, property, occupancy, location, market conditions, and lender guidelines. For current options tailored to you,<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a consultation</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/"> apply online</a>.</p><p>Ready to explore your options?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> with a loan advisor.</p>		
					<h2>How This Asset-Based Loan Purchase Enabled a Quick-Close on Premium Property in Competitive Market</h2>				
		<p>Jennifer L., a 52-year-old investment banker based in Miami, had built substantial wealth over a 25-year career in private equity and wealth management. With a significant portfolio of liquid assets including stocks, bonds, mutual funds, and retirement accounts, she was financially secure and ready to purchase her dream waterfront home on Biscayne Bay—a luxury property that would serve as her primary residence as she transitioned toward semi-retirement over the next few years.</p><p>Jennifer had substantial liquid assets but her income situation was complex. She received strong compensation from her firm including partnership distributions, carried interest from investments, and deferred compensation structures, but her tax returns didn't accurately reflect her true financial capacity. Much of her wealth was strategically held in investment portfolios rather than showing as traditional W-2 income. Additionally, she wanted to preserve her investment positions during a strong market cycle rather than liquidating substantial holdings to purchase the home outright with cash.</p><p>When Jennifer found the perfect waterfront property—a luxury home with direct bay access in Coconut Grove—she needed to act quickly in Miami's competitive high-end real estate market. Traditional mortgage lenders wanted extensive income documentation including two years of tax returns, employer verification, and complex explanations of her compensation structure. The documentation requirements and approval timeline would likely cause her to lose the property to another buyer willing to close faster.</p><p>Jennifer needed a<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/asset-based-loan/"> financing solution</a> that recognized her substantial financial resources without requiring traditional income verification or extended underwriting timelines.</p><p><b>Facing similar challenges?</b><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> to explore your options.</p><h2><b>The Challenge: Why Traditional Lenders Couldn't Process This Purchase Quickly Enough</b></h2><p>Jennifer approached two conventional lenders confident that her strong financial position would make approval straightforward. She had substantial liquid assets, excellent credit, significant net worth, and appropriate down payment funds already verified and ready to transfer. She'd already been pre-qualified by her real estate agent's preferred lender and felt confident moving forward with offers on luxury properties.</p><p>Both lenders immediately requested extensive income documentation that would require weeks to compile and verify.</p><h3><b>What Income Documentation Did Traditional Purchase Lenders Require?</b></h3><p>Traditional mortgage lenders demanded two years of complete tax returns with all schedules, employer verification letters from her firm, detailed written explanations of partnership distributions and how they're calculated, comprehensive documentation of deferred compensation structures and vesting schedules, and projections of future income based on past performance. The complexity of her compensation structure—including carried interest from investments, partnership K-1 tax forms, and deferred payments spanning multiple years—created extensive underwriting questions that would require substantial time to resolve.</p><p>"I felt frustrated by the disconnect between my actual financial capacity and what lenders were focusing on," Jennifer explained. "I have substantial liquid assets—diversified investment portfolios worth significantly more than the home I wanted to purchase. But lenders kept asking for extensive income documentation and detailed tax return analysis. The process was going to take weeks or potentially months, and I'd almost certainly lose the property while waiting for approval."</p><h3><b>Why Was Timeline Critical in Miami's Luxury Market?</b></h3><p>The timeline challenge was absolutely critical. The waterfront property Jennifer wanted had attracted multiple interested buyers—all financially qualified and eager to secure the property. The seller strongly preferred quick-close transactions and wanted minimal financing contingencies that could delay closing or potentially fall through. Jennifer's traditional mortgage approval would require extensive underwriting, multiple documentation rounds, likely follow-up questions about complex compensation structures, and would probably take several weeks minimum—making her offer significantly less competitive than cash buyers or buyers with simpler financing already approved.</p><p>"This wasn't about whether I could afford the home—I clearly could without question," Jennifer said. "It was about whether I could get financing approved quickly enough to compete with other buyers in a competitive luxury market. Traditional mortgage underwriting timelines simply weren't going to work in Miami's high-end real estate market where premium properties move quickly and sellers strongly prefer certainty over highest price."</p><h3><b>Why Did Jennifer Want to Avoid Liquidating Investments?</b></h3><p>Additionally, Jennifer strongly preferred to keep her substantial investment portfolio intact rather than liquidating positions to buy the home outright with cash. The market was performing well, her portfolio was positioned strategically according to her wealth advisor's recommendations, and selling positions would trigger significant capital gains taxes—essentially paying substantial fees to the government just to access her own wealth. She wanted to leverage her assets strategically without liquidating them—using them as demonstrated financial strength for loan approval while keeping them invested and working for her wealth growth.</p><p><b>Experiencing similar frustration with traditional lending timelines?</b><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> to discuss alternative solutions.</p><h2><b>The Discovery: How Jennifer Found Asset-Based Purchase Lending</b></h2><p>While discussing her financing challenges with her wealth advisor, Jennifer learned about<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/asset-based-loan/"> asset-based loan programs</a> designed specifically for high-net-worth individuals with substantial liquid assets. Her advisor explained that these programs qualify borrowers based on investment portfolio values rather than traditional income documentation, offering dramatically faster approval timelines perfect for competitive luxury markets where timing is critical.</p><h3><b>What Made Jennifer Skeptical About Fast Approval?</b></h3><p>Intrigued by the concept but initially skeptical, Jennifer scheduled a consultation with a loan advisor specializing in asset-based lending for high-net-worth clients. She doubted that any mortgage process could move quickly enough to compete effectively with cash buyers who could close in days rather than weeks. But her wealth advisor's strong recommendation and the specific focus on portfolio-based qualification convinced her to explore the option seriously.</p><h3><b>How Do Asset-Based Purchase Lenders Work Differently Than Traditional Lenders?</b></h3><p>During the consultation, the advisor explained how asset-based loans work fundamentally differently than traditional mortgages. Instead of analyzing tax returns and employment income documentation, asset-based purchase lenders evaluate liquid asset portfolios—stocks, bonds, mutual funds, retirement accounts, and other investment holdings. The loan qualification is based entirely on total portfolio value and asset quality rather than employment income or tax returns showing complex compensation structures.</p><p>"That conversation changed my entire approach to financing the purchase," Jennifer said. "The advisor explained that with my substantial investment portfolio, I could qualify for financing without providing tax returns, employer letters, or detailed income explanations. The focus would be purely on my liquid assets—which were more than sufficient to support the mortgage comfortably. And most importantly, the approval process could happen in days rather than weeks or months, making my offer competitive with cash buyers."</p><h3><b>What Was Jennifer's "Aha Moment" About Asset-Based Lending?</b></h3><p>The advisor also explained that asset-based loans preserve investment positions strategically. Rather than liquidating portfolio holdings to buy with cash—triggering substantial capital gains taxes and removing assets from the market during favorable conditions—Jennifer could use her portfolio as qualification strength while keeping it fully invested and working for her. This approach aligned perfectly with her wealth management strategy and her advisor's recommendations.</p><p>Jennifer learned that asset-based lending works particularly well for clients like her: high net worth, substantial liquid assets, complex income structures, and urgent need for quick approval timelines. The program recognized that financial capacity comes in different forms, and that substantial investment portfolios demonstrate financial strength just as effectively as traditional W-2 income—often more reliably.</p><h2><b>The Solution: Asset-Based Loan Purchase Approval Process</b></h2><p>Jennifer worked closely with her loan advisor to assemble the required documentation for an asset-based loan purchase application. The process focused entirely on her liquid asset portfolio rather than income documentation, dramatically simplifying requirements and accelerating the timeline substantially.</p><h3><b>What Documentation Did Jennifer Provide for Her Purchase?</b></h3><p><b>Documentation provided:</b></p><ul><li>Comprehensive investment account statements showing substantial portfolio value</li><li>Detailed asset portfolio breakdown including stocks, bonds, mutual funds, ETFs, and retirement accounts</li><li>Account statements from multiple brokerage firms and investment managers</li><li>Excellent credit score with strong payment history across all accounts</li><li>Appropriate down payment funds verified and ready to transfer</li><li>Strong cash reserves beyond down payment and closing costs</li><li>Minimal income documentation—no tax returns or employer verification required</li><li>Executed purchase contract for waterfront property in Coconut Grove</li></ul><h3><b>How Fast Did Jennifer's Asset-Based Purchase Approval Happen?</b></h3><p><b>The approval timeline:</b></p><ol><li><b>Initial consultation (Day 1)</b> — Discussed asset-based qualification and luxury property purchase goals</li><li><b>Asset portfolio review (Days 1-2)</b> — Analyzed total liquid asset values and portfolio composition</li><li><b>Pre-approval issued (Day 3)</b> — Approved to make offers based on asset portfolio strength</li><li><b>Property identified and offer submitted (Week 2)</b> — Found perfect waterfront home, made strong offer</li><li><b>Offer accepted (Week 2, Day 3)</b> — Seller accepted offer based on quick-close capability</li><li><b>Purchase contract executed (Week 2, Day 4)</b> — Signed purchase agreement</li><li><b>Property appraisal ordered (Week 2, Day 5)</b> — Scheduled appraisal immediately</li><li><b>Final asset verification (Week 3, Days 1-2)</b> — Confirmed current portfolio values</li><li><b>Appraisal completed (Week 3, Day 4)</b> — Property appraised at purchase price</li><li><b>Final underwriting (Week 3, Days 5-6)</b> — Completed remaining verification</li><li><b>Clear to close (Week 3, Day 7)</b> — Final approval granted</li><li><b>Closing completed (Week 4, Day 1)</b> — Closed on waterfront home in under 4 weeks</li></ol><h3><b>How Did Asset-Based Purchase Lenders Evaluate Jennifer's Qualification?</b></h3><p>The asset-based purchase lender evaluated Jennifer's substantial liquid investment portfolio and determined that her total financial resources provided more than sufficient capacity to support the mortgage comfortably. Rather than calculating traditional debt-to-income ratios based on complex partnership distributions and deferred compensation, they assessed her total portfolio value and concluded that her financial strength was exceptional.</p><p>This approach recognized that high-net-worth individuals often structure wealth in investments rather than maximizing current taxable income, and that portfolio value demonstrates financial capacity more reliably than income documentation for this demographic.</p><h3><b>What Made Jennifer's Application Exceptionally Strong?</b></h3><p>Several factors made Jennifer's asset-based purchase application particularly strong. Her excellent credit score demonstrated financial responsibility. Her substantial liquid asset portfolio exceeded the property value significantly. Her diversified holdings across multiple asset classes showed sophisticated wealth management. Her appropriate down payment funds were verified and ready. And her quick-close capability made her offer attractive to sellers.</p><p>The combination positioned Jennifer as an ideal borrower for asset-based qualification—high financial capacity, low risk, and ready to close efficiently.</p><p><b>Ready to purchase your dream property?</b><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/purchase-inquiry/"> Submit a purchase inquiry</a> to discuss your scenario.</p><h2><b>The Results: How Did Asset-Based Financing Enable Jennifer's Luxury Home Purchase?</b></h2><p>Jennifer closed on her waterfront home in under four weeks from initial offer—competing successfully against other buyers and securing the property in Miami's competitive luxury market. She purchased her dream home with direct Biscayne Bay access in Coconut Grove while keeping her substantial investment portfolio fully invested and working for her.</p><h3><b>What Were the Final Terms of Jennifer's Purchase?</b></h3><p><b>Final loan outcome:</b></p><ul><li>Approved substantial financing based entirely on investment portfolio qualification</li><li>Competitive interest rate given her excellent credit and strong financial position</li><li>Favorable long-term fixed-rate structure</li><li>Appropriate down payment structure for luxury property</li><li>Timeline: Under 4 weeks from offer acceptance to closing</li><li>Portfolio remained fully invested—no liquidation required</li><li>No capital gains taxes triggered from asset sales</li><li>Quick-close capability made offer competitive with cash buyers</li></ul><h3><b>How Did Asset-Based Qualification Compare to Traditional Lending?</b></h3><p><b>Traditional purchase lender vs. asset-based purchase lender comparison:</b></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><b>Qualification Factor</b></p></td><td><p><b>Traditional Lender</b></p></td><td><p><b>Asset-Based Purchase Lender</b></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Primary qualification basis</b></p></td><td><p>Complex income documentation</p></td><td><p>Liquid investment portfolio value</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Tax returns required</b></p></td><td><p>Two years with all schedules</p></td><td><p>Not required</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Employer verification</b></p></td><td><p>Required</p></td><td><p>Not required</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Income complexity</b></p></td><td><p>Extensive analysis required</p></td><td><p>Not applicable</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Partnership K-1 explanations</b></p></td><td><p>Required</p></td><td><p>Not required</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Portfolio consideration</b></p></td><td><p>Secondary or ignored</p></td><td><p>Primary qualification factor</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Approval timeline</b></p></td><td><p>Extended (weeks/months)</p></td><td><p>Streamlined (under 4 weeks)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Competitive positioning</b></p></td><td><p>Weak vs. cash buyers</p></td><td><p>Strong vs. cash buyers ✅</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Property goal</b></p></td><td><p>Likely lost to faster buyers ❌</p></td><td><p>SECURED ✅</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Portfolio preservation</b></p></td><td><p>Not considered</p></td><td><p>Explicitly enabled ✅</p></td></tr></tbody></table><h3><b>What Immediate Benefits Did Jennifer Experience?</b></h3><p>"Without asset-based purchase lending, I would have lost this property to a cash buyer while waiting for traditional mortgage approval," Jennifer explained. "The seller wanted certainty and speed—both of which asset-based lending provided. I was able to compete effectively without liquidating my investment portfolio and paying substantial capital gains taxes. It was the perfect solution for my situation."</p><p>Jennifer moved into her dream waterfront home with direct bay access, spectacular views, and the lifestyle amenities she'd envisioned for years. Her investment portfolio continued performing without disruption. She avoided triggering considerable capital gains taxes. And she secured the property in a competitive market where timing was critical.</p><h3><b>How Does This Purchase Fit Into Jennifer's Bigger Wealth Strategy?</b></h3><p>Jennifer views this purchase as part of her broader wealth and lifestyle strategy. The waterfront home provides immediate substantial lifestyle value and enjoyment while also serving as a real estate holding that will likely appreciate significantly over time in Miami's desirable Coconut Grove neighborhood. Her investment portfolio continues growing uninterrupted, compounding wealth without the disruption of large liquidations. And she's maintained the flexibility and liquidity that sophisticated wealth management requires.</p><p>"For high-net-worth individuals, asset-based lending makes perfect sense," Jennifer added. "Why liquidate performing investments, trigger substantial capital gains taxes, and remove assets from the market just to buy real estate with cash? Asset-based loans let you leverage your portfolio strength intelligently, keep investments working and compounding, and maintain the liquidity and flexibility that sophisticated wealth management requires. It's how financially smart people approach real estate purchases when they have substantial assets."</p><h3><b>What Future Opportunities Has Jennifer Created?</b></h3><p>Jennifer has established a relationship with asset-based lenders that will serve her well for future real estate opportunities—whether that's a vacation property in the mountains, investment real estate for passive income, or helping her adult children purchase homes using her assets for qualification. She understands that her substantial portfolio provides financing flexibility whenever opportunities arise.</p><p>Additionally, if she decides to access home equity in the future for renovations, investments, or other purposes, she knows that<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/asset-based-loan-cash-out-refinance/"> cash-out refinancing</a> or a<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/heloc/"> HELOC</a> would be available—all leveraging her financial strength efficiently.</p><p><b>Ready to get started on your luxury home purchase?</b><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/"> Get approved</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a call</a> to discuss your situation.</p><h2><b>Exploring Other Asset-Based Loan Options?</b></h2><p>While Jennifer used an asset-based loan for her luxury home purchase, asset-based financing works for multiple scenarios:</p><ul><li><b>Need to refinance?</b> See how a<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/asset-based-loan-refinance/"> retired executive used asset-based loan refinance to improve terms</a> without income verification</li><li><b>Want to access equity?</b> See how an<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/asset-based-loan-cash-out-refinance/"> entrepreneur used asset-based cash-out refinance for business capital</a> while preserving investments</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/">View all case studies</a> to find success stories matching your financial situation</li></ul><h2><b>Key Takeaways for High-Net-Worth Borrowers</b></h2><h3><b>What Can High-Net-Worth Individuals Learn from This Asset-Based Loan Purchase Success?</b></h3><ul><li><b>Asset-based loans qualify borrowers based on liquid investment portfolio values, not traditional income</b>—perfect for high-net-worth individuals with complex compensation structures or substantial wealth in investments. Portfolio value demonstrates financial capacity more reliably than tax returns showing partnership distributions or deferred compensation (<a href="https://www.investor.gov/">SEC investment account regulations</a>)<p> </p></li><li><b>Quick approval timelines make asset-based financing competitive with cash offers in luxury markets</b>—streamlined documentation and faster underwriting enable closes in under 4 weeks rather than traditional timelines of 45-60+ days. Speed creates competitive advantage in markets where properties move quickly<p> </p></li><li><b>Preserving investment positions avoids unnecessary capital gains taxes and keeps assets working</b>—borrowing against portfolio strength is often significantly smarter than liquidating performing investments and triggering substantial tax consequences. Jennifer's strategy saved considerable taxes while keeping investments compounding (<a href="https://www.irs.gov/taxtopics/tc409">IRS capital gains tax guidance</a>)<p> </p></li><li><b>High-net-worth borrowers benefit from flexible documentation requirements</b>—no tax returns, no employer verification, no income complexity analysis; focus purely on straightforward asset verification that moves quickly<p> </p></li><li><b>Asset-based lending aligns with sophisticated wealth management principles</b>—leverage when advantageous, maintain portfolio positions during favorable markets, preserve liquidity and flexibility for opportunities<p> </p></li><li><b>Excellent credit profiles unlock competitive rates even with alternative qualification methods</b>—strong credit helped Jennifer secure favorable pricing on asset-based financing despite complex income structure<p> </p></li></ul><p><b>Have questions about asset-based lending for luxury purchases?</b><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> with a loan advisor experienced in high-net-worth financing.</p><h2><b>Alternative Loan Programs for High-Net-Worth Borrowers</b></h2><p>If an asset-based loan purchase isn't the perfect fit for your situation, consider these alternative financing options:</p><ul><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/bank-statement-loan/">Bank Statement Loan</a> – Qualify using bank deposits for business owners or self-employed professionals</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/dscr-loan/">DSCR Loan</a> – Investment property financing based on rental income, no personal income verification required</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/portfolio-loan/">Portfolio Loan</a> – Finance multiple properties efficiently with flexible terms</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/jumbo-loan/">Jumbo Loan</a> – High-balance financing for luxury properties with traditional documentation</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/foreign-national-loan/">Foreign National Loan</a> – Financing for international buyers without U.S. credit or income history</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/non-qm-loan/">Non-QM Loan</a> – Flexible qualification options for unique financial situations</li></ul><p><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/">Explore all loan programs</a> to find your best option.</p><p>Want to explore your luxury purchase strategy?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/discovery-quiz/"> Take our discovery quiz</a> to clarify your goals.</p><h2><b>Helpful Asset-Based Loan Purchase Resources</b></h2><p><b>Learn more about this loan program:</b></p><ul><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/asset-based-loan/">Complete Asset-Based Loan Guide</a> – Detailed requirements and qualification guidelines for portfolio-based purchases</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-calculator/asset-based-loan-calculator">Asset-Based Loan Calculator</a> – Estimate qualification based on your portfolio value</li></ul><p><b>Similar success stories:</b></p><ul><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/asset-based-loan-refinance/">How a retired executive used asset-based refinance to improve terms</a> – Refinancing success with portfolio assets</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/asset-based-loan-cash-out-refinance/">Entrepreneur's asset-based cash-out refinance</a> – Accessing equity for business investment</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/">View all case studies</a> – Browse by financial situation and goals</li></ul><p><b>External authoritative resources:</b></p><ul><li><a href="https://www.investor.gov/">SEC Investment Account Regulations</a> – Understanding investment account types and portfolio values</li><li><a href="https://www.irs.gov/taxtopics/tc409">IRS Capital Gains Tax Guidance</a> – Tax considerations for investment liquidation decisions</li><li><a href="https://www.finra.org/investors">FINRA Investor Resources</a> – Financial industry regulatory authority investor protection</li></ul><p><b>Ready to get started?</b></p><ul><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/">Apply online</a> – Start your purchase application today</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/">Schedule a consultation</a> – Discuss your portfolio and luxury purchase goals with experienced advisors</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/discovery-quiz/">Take the discovery quiz</a> – Deep dive into your wealth-building strategy</li></ul><p>Need local expertise?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/get-a-local-introduction/"> Get introduced to trusted partners</a> including luxury real estate specialists and wealth advisors.</p><p><b>Disclosure:</b> <a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/nexa-mortgage-partnership/"  data-wpil-monitor-id="311">NEXA Mortgage</a>, LLC dba Stairway Mortgage — NMLS #1660690 • Equal Housing Lender. Applications are handled by state-licensed Mortgage Loan Originators; you will be matched with an MLO licensed in your state. Not all products are available in all states. See our<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/licenses-disclosures"> Licenses &amp; Disclosures</a> page for state-specific information. This case study is for educational and illustrative purposes only. Scenarios, borrowers, and loan terms may be hypothetical and are used to demonstrate potential financing solutions. Not a commitment to lend. All loans are subject to credit approval, program availability, and underwriting guidelines. Interest rates, fees, loan amounts, and other terms are examples and do not represent current offers or market rates. Actual terms vary by applicant profile, property, market conditions, and lender guidelines, and may change without notice. Asset-based lending involves pledging liquid assets as collateral or qualification basis; specific lender requirements vary regarding asset types, liquidity, and portfolio composition. For current terms specific to your situation, please<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a consultation</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/"> apply online</a>. NMLS Consumer Access:<a href="https://www.nmlsconsumeraccess.org/"> https://www.nmlsconsumeraccess.org/</a></p>		
